The paper involves the compilation of a subset of Prolog into an executable form suitable for a quantum annealer, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of constraint logic programming also suggests a potential fit for the data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) categories. Finally, the evaluation of the approach on a quantum annealer suggests a potential fit for the computing and computation (cs.CC) category.
